<http://ots.local/thesaurus/apqc/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7934> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/apqc/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7717> ;
    skos:definition "Define Customer Acquisition Strategy & Plan processes establish the activities that manage the enterprises preferences for customers, and processes for bringing new customers or clients to the business. <br/>The goal of this set of processes is to create a systematic, sustainable acquisition strategy that can evolve with new trends and changes. It allows the business to: Make money to meet costs, and reinvest in growth, and show evidence of traction for outside parties such as investors, partners, and influencers.<br/>This process was named - Customer Acquisition Strategy & Planning<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:apqc ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7934" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Customer Acquisition Strategy & Plan"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/apqc/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7935> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/apqc/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7717> ;
    skos:definition "Define Customer Retention Strategy & Plan defines the activities that enable the organization to provide and extract more value from existing customer base.<br/>The set of processes enable develop a strategic management plan with a set of actions that keeps customers the organization has invested into acquiring. <br/>The strategy and plan help deliver services that are consistent with the organization value proposition and brand. This includes developing programs to increase customer loyalty and decreasing turnover.<br/><br/>This process was named Customer Retention Strategy & Planning<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:apqc ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7935" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Customer Retention Strategy & Plan"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/apqc/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7936> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/apqc/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7717> ;
    skos:definition "The set of processes to plan the delivery of a sustained or increasing customer satisfaction by having more positive interactions with customers.<br/>It can be through any channel, from in person, to online, to over the phone. Great strategies take customer engagement from reactive to proactive.<br/><br/>This process was named Customer Engagement Strategy & Planning<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:apqc ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7936" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Customer Engagement Strategy & Plan"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/apqc/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7937> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/apqc/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7717> ;
    skos:definition "Define Customer Support Strategy & Plan processes ensures that a Customer Service Strategy is a thorough plan to handle customer interactions. It lets the organization provide a consistent customer experience throughout the customer journey.<br/>A customer support plan establishes methods and techniques to deeply examine customers' perceptions and expectations of the organization, and guides the company through the process of bringing its customer service activities in line with customers' needs.<br/>Improved customer experience results in a more loyal customer base. Loyal customers buy more often, spend more, and refer their friends and family to the organization either through social structures.<br/><br/>This process was Customer Support Strategy & Planning<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:apqc ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7937" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Customer Support Strategy & Plan"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/apqc/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7939> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/apqc/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA3_EA7896> ;
    skos:definition "Not used for this process element<br/>"@en ;
